inn1.comm: Two slips in place and Gul lands the first delivery in the zone outside off stump. Gibbs leans forward,  covers his off stump before shouldering arms
nip backer, coming in from just outside off stump and Gibbs leans forward, bat and pad close together, to defend.
beatem Fuller and just outside off stump, Gibbs went for a expansive off drive and the ball threaded the bat and pad gap and went zipping past the off stump
back to the good length, around the off stump, Gibbs opens the bat-face to steer it  to backward point
fullish, outside off stump, driven to cover
on the off stump again, another forward defense from Gibbs
swings away outside off, full in length, Smith lets it go past him
Fullish, outside off stump and Smith gets on to the front foot in a flash and creams it through wide mid-off
closer to the off stump, pushed to mid-off
too full, a gift outside off and Smith drills it through the gap between cover and mid-off.
shout for lbw as Tanvir brings the ball back in this time. It landed on a length, around the middle and swung in to strike the pad. Going down leg side though.

streaky edge past second slip. Full and swinging away from Gibbs who went for the length and tried driving it through cover. The swing meant the ball took the outside edge and flew past the second slip fielder
in the corridor outside off stump, full in length and left alone. SA 10 for 0.
short in length, just outside off stump, holding its line, guided to backward point
short in length, closer to the off stump and cuts away, Gibbs lets it fly past him
overpitched delivery on the off stump line and Gibbs caresses it straight down the ground.

drags back the length and slows up the pace, around 123 k, on a length and shaping away, Gibbs leans forward, initially looking to drive before checking his stroke and gets a outside edge, one bounce to Younis Khan at second slip
fuller, on the middle, driven to mid-on.
and he slips this well down the leg side. Wide called. Smith asks for people to sit down behind the sight screen
beaten Full and just outside off stump, the bat comes down from say third slip and goes outside the line of the ball.
on the off and middle, pushed to the off side
Full and on the middle and leg, Smith shuffles across, gets outside the line of the ball and clips it away to fine leg boundary
fullish, outside off and driven straight to short cover. Smith had driven Sohail for two boundaries through the off side and so, they have moved the second slip out to short cover
short in length, cutting away a touch outside off and Smith shuffles across before pushing it to right of short cover
low dipping full toss outside off stump, Smith makes contact with the bottom-half of the bat and the ball rolls towards mid-off. Too much bottom-hand and the bat face shut a tad early
short in length, homing in on the middle and off, Gibbs pushes it quietly into cover
on a length, around off stump, no movement and Gibbs eases it to cover
length delivery on the off stump, holds its line, Gibbs doesn't move into the line, just stands there to push it to the off side
And he is beaten.  It landed on a length, around the off stump and cut away , Gibbs, again not really into the line, has a tentative poke at it and is beaten. It went off the seam
on a length, around off stump, Gibbs plonks his front foot across and pushes the ball into the cover region

almost dragged on. Fuller in length, outside off stump, inviting Gibbs to go for a drive and he does; perhaps too hard at the delivery, the bottom-hand takes over, the bat-face shuts and he gets a inside-edge onto the pad.
drifting on to the legs and Smith clips it away easily through midwicket
again on the pads, another flick but this time there is a short midwicket and he comes in the way
shifts his line to outside off stump and Smith mistimes a drive to mid-off

Another length delivery, on the off stump line, coming in a touch, Smith tries to drive on the up and gets a inside edge to pad. Again too much bottom-hand and the bat coming down at an angle. That's the way Smith plays

Charges out as he backs to the leg side and tries to heave a length delivery over mid-off but fails to connect. Again typical Smith- except the part about failing to connect ie. He likes to charge the seamers now and then in the ODI game
short in length, on the stumps, pulled away for a single
banged in short, on the off and middle line, angling away but Smith stands up tall to play a feisty pull shot through midwicket
fuller, as expected, on the middle and leg, moves in a touch and that late movement defeats Smith's intended on drive and the ball rolls back to the bowler
slower one, 120.8 kmph, on the stumps and Smith leans forward to dead-bat it

Full in length, on the middle and leg, Smith drives it straight down the track and falls short of Gul who lunges forward to 'catch' it and it races away between his legs. Malik gives the chase and manages to pull the ball back just in time.
cracking cut. Slightly short in length, just outside off stump, enough for Gibbs to rock back and play a lovely cut past point. That one raced away
full and swinging in on the middle stump line, Smith helps it along with the angle to long leg
Charges out, reaches the pitch of a length delivery on the middle stump line and drives inside-out over mid-off . Fab strike. He made it look easy and elegant.
Runs are coming thick and fast here. Full and wide, another free gift and Gibbs thrashes it through extra cover. Now the fine leg is in the circle and we have a man at sweeper cover
on the middle and leg, turned to square leg
overpitched, on the off stump, driven to mid-off
And he is gone now. Edged to Akmal. Full in length, holding its line just outside off stump and Gibbs had a poke at it. Fatal. Gone.
back of a length outside off, he gets back and defends it to point
fuller delivery, now Kallis gets a firm stride in and defends
full outside off again, he leans forward and lazily drives to cover
back of a length, a touch wider this time, and Kallis steers it wide of backward point to get off the mark
good movement, pitching on leg stump and swinging away from Smith, who shapes to flick and gets a leading-edge along the ground towards point
lovely delivery, pitching on a length and moving away, doing enough to suck a loose-footed Kallis driving and missing the line of the ball
pushed across Kallis wider this time and he leaves well enough alone
full outside off stump, Kallis gets the front foot forward and steers it to backward point
full outside off, no movement, Kallis uses the feet and drives to mid-off
full again, this time he drives it wide of Rao at mid-off and calls for the single
fullish length, Smith gets out and checks the drive to mid-off
slower ball, back of a length outside off stump, Kallis leaves it be
shuffles around in his crease, looking to come down and across, and Gul bowls it wide of off stump, forcing Kallis to leave it be again
back of a length, pitching and going on straight to beat Kallis' back-foot poke
slower ball, Gul rolling the fingers across the seam and moving it in off a short length, Kallis again hops and opens the face of the bat and misses the line
back of a length, good lift, Kallis gets behind it and defends watchfully
again Kallis moves in his crease and Gul bowls it short and wide, only for Kallis to get across and watch it into Akmal's gloves
walks well outside off stump, the ball slants in and clips Smith's pads for a leg-bye
angled across Kallis on a length, he gets forward and shoulders arms
much fuller now, moving in from off stump and almost getting through Kallis, who hastily shapes to on drive and squeezes it to cover
full outside off, he leans into it and square-drives to point

walks across the stumps, Tanvir pitches on a good length and catches Kallis in front of off stump as he looks to flick, ball doesnt come in a lot but they all go up in appeal .. theres a noise but the umpire isnt interested ... close shout, may just have been outside the line of impact
full and wide, Smith reaches for it and drives to point
loose shot from Kallis, who doesnt move his feet and flashes at one outside off stump only to get beaten once again by Gul
now Gul serves up a very low full toss outside off, but Kallis cant put it away, driving to cover
back of a length on off stump, hint of movement into Kallis, who drives back to Gul
full on off stump, Kallis drives well but cant beat extra cover
now thats timed well! Gul overpitches wide and Kallis cracks it off the middle of the bat, freeing the arms and picking the gap between cover and point
good length delivery, coming into middle from off, Kallis defends and gets an inside-edge back towards square leg for one
full on middle and off, he gets forward and defends with an inside-edge to square leg again ... Tanvir striving for movement
full outside off, driven to mid-off with good timing
on the middle stump line, angling away, Kallis stays adjacent to the line and drives inside out to left of cover
full and outside off stump, Kallis again stays adjacent and frees his arms at the width. He carves it over cover. Imperious.
fuller, straighter, Kallis jabs it away to the on side for a single
on a length, coming in towards off stump and Smith punches it to mid-on
short in length, on the leg and middle line and it spins a touch, Kallis adjusts to the spin by moving his wrists and drops the ball in front of him

he strikes almost immediately. Loopy flighted delivery outside off stump and Kallis again goes for an inside-out cover drive but can't keep it down and it goes to left of short cover where its safely pouched. Drinks on the field
It spun back in from outside off stump and rapped de Villiers on the pad. Going down leg side
turns away from the off stump, steered to cover point for a single
lands outside leg stump and spins down leg side. Wide called. The ball is turning quite a bit here
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
beaten. turns across Smith who lunges forward to defend and is beaten. Sharp turn on offer.
short in length, outside off stump, de Villiers shuffles right across, ends up outside off and defends back down the track
full and well outside off stump, going with the angle, left alone
again angling away from de Villiers who shoulders arms
full in length, closer to the off stump, driven to mid-off
fullish, outside off, slanting away and square driven to deep cover
on the middle stump line, coming in with the angle, worked straight to midwicket
lands on the middle and leg, turns in slowly, pushed down the track
lands well outside off, holds up a touch as it spins away, flat-batted to cover point
loopy delivery outside off stump, sucking de Villiers into a square drive and he edges it past the second slip

shout for lbw. Slider coming in towards off and middle, de Villers goes back and is cramped up by the incoming delivery. The ball clips him on the back thigh pad before striking the bat. The umpire Bowden must have thought it would have gone just over. Close.
on the off stump line, defended to the off side
goes back to punch through the off side for a single
on the middle and off stump, angling away, pushed to cover
bit of width outside off stump and that's de Villier's area. And he leans forward to square drive through cover point. The bottom-hand came off the handle at impact
on the middle and off, on a length, defended to the off side
on the off stump line, angling away again, steered to point.
straighter and that allows de Villiers to clip it past square leg
back to regular programming. On a length, around middle and off, angling away and de Villiers leans forward, bat and pad close together, to defend
lands on the leg stump line and turns down leg side. Smith takes it early and punches it past square leg. The subcontinental batsmen would have waited for the turn and played it to fine leg region
turning away from de Villiers, full in length, inviting a drive - there is a slip in place- but he resists
leans forward to drive this time and gets it past cover
short in length, outside off stump, gets back and across to cut it left of sweeper cover where Yaseer Hameed makes the stop. "Koi nahi, Shahid Bhai, Koi nahi," says Akmal.
shuffles right across the sticks to get behind a legbreak, that ended up outside off stump and defends
full pitched outside off stump - delivered from the classical side-on position, driven to mid-off
on the off stump line, coming in a touch, mistimes a drive to midwicket. He was intending to go straight but the bat-face turned at the last minute
outside off, on a length and de Villiers gets his bat down straight this time and drives to mid-off
full again, on the off stump line and square driven to point

what a stunner from Afridi at short midwicket. It was full in length, on the middle stump line, coming in a touch, de Villiers drove loosely, the bottom-hand came off the handle, the bat-face again turned and it went uppishly to the right of Afridi who flung himself in the air, both feet off the ground, to pluck it inches off the turf. A Youtube moment.
low dipping full toss, around 138 kmph, on the middle stump line, jabbed back down the track
turns in from just outside off, turned to midwicket
googly on the middle and off, fullish, squeezed to point
loopy delivery outside off, dipping rapidly on Kemp who tries to take it on the full and drive through the off side and instead, gets a inside-edge behind square leg
lands on the leg stump line, on a length and turns back in, rather away from Smith, who jabs at it and gets a outside edge to the off side
gets off the strike - not that he has got much of the strike today- with a single to backward point
outside off stump, turning away, left alone
full and slanting away from Smith who steers it to backward point
on the middle and off line, off a length, turned to left of midwicket for a single
on the off stump line, defended on the front foot
fuller, coming in a touch, on the middle and leg, squeezed to long leg
on the off stump line, again on a length, pushed to the off side and Rao gets across to make the stop
walks down the track even as he shuffles across a touch and flicks a full length delivery on the middle to long leg
floated outside off stump, that bottom-hand again and the ball is turned to midwicket
outside off again, defended to the on side/
dropped by Akmal. It was a googly outside off stump, Smith stabbed at it and edged it to Akmal who fails to hold on. The ball pops up and it falls between a lunging Akmal and Younis at first slip.
picks up a single with a drive to long on
flighted delivery outside leg stump, turns in and Kemp pushes at it, too early and the ball rolls to the leg side. Not the best way to play a ball turning across.
on the off stump line, steered to the off side for a single
banged in short and Smith pulls it to fine leg.
off cutter outside off stump, pushed to cover. There is a direct hit at the striker's end but no overthrows result.
slower one, 121.1 kmph, short in length and Kemp is made to wait on the ball before defending it back to Rao
may be he should have let it remain in its place as he plays and misses at a length delivery outside off stump. A tentative poke and he is beaten
And again. Closer to the off stump and he stabs at it but inside the line and the ball teased the outside edge.
quickish, on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket
slower in the air this time, on the middle again, turned to midwicket
flighted legbreak, outside off stump and Smith plays it with the turn to deep square leg
on the middle and off stump line, Kemp leans forward to paddle it away for a single
fullish, on the off and middle, sliding away, squeezed to mid-off region for a single
full and on the middle, just short of the blockhole, jabbed away to the off side
slow off cutter, on the middle and leg, worked to midwicket
slower one, short in length, another off cutter, Smith walks down the track to wrist it behind square for a single
on a length, around the middle stump line, turned to midwicket
another off cutter, just outside off stump, Kemp waits on the ball before chopping it away to third man
off cutter on the middle and off line, steered to cover point for a single.
low full toss, on the middle stump, Kemp must feel he has missed out there as he drives it straight to mid-on
tries to sweep  a delivery that landed outside off stump and is struck on the pad
connects with his sweep this time and picks up a single
runs diagonally across and floats a delivery outside off stump, a tad short in length and kemp is beaten on the cut
on the stumps, paddled away to short fine leg region for a single
lands outside off, on a length and turns sharply, Smith waits for the turn this time before wristing it to fine leg
another paddle shot from Kemp. He must love rowing. (Sick I know.. sorry!) It was on the middle stump and he lapped it around the corner for a single.
short of length, on the off stump line, punched back to the bowler
on the middle and leg line, full in length, tickled to right of midwicket for a single.
stands outside the crease and waits on the slower delivery before guiding to past backward point
Kemp stands inside the crease, on the middle and leg, misses a glance and it runs off the pad. 100 is up for SA. 100 for 3. The partnership has reached 23
fuller and outside off stump, Smith goes for a cover drive but gets a thickish outside edge and down to wide third man
on a length, around the off stump line, guided to point for a single
beaten. Big turn. It landed on the off and middle and spun sharply past the forward prod
fuller, turning away from the off stump line and Kemp again tries to paddle it but fails to make contact
another attempt at paddle shot and the ball bounces up to strike him on the pad
leans forward to defend to off side
Big turn again. Beaten. It drifted in the air, landed on the middle and spun across sharply. Kemp stabbed at it and is beaten
quicker, a tad short and that allows Kemp to punch it to extra cover
good length delivery outside off stump, Kemp stands and aggressively drives towards mid-off, failing to beat the fielder
this one comes back off a length and Kemp drops it sofly towards backward point and Smith urges the quick single, seeing that Kemp is struggling
and thats one reason Smith wanted the strike! He walks down the track to a good-length delivery and smears it back over Rao's head for a one-bounce four, the first for 12 overs
slower ball as Rao rolls the fingers over the ball, pitching on a good length again, but this time Smith waits for it and pushes it towards backward point
Rao strays down leg stump and Kemp turns him into the gap and picks up a single down to Afridi, jogging around from fine leg
good length outside off, Smith is early into his shot and checks the drive to mid-off
gets well outside off stump, kneels down, and sweeps into the ground in front of short fine leg for one
tossed up full, Kemp too reaches forward and paddles it from middle and off for a single into the gap at short fine leg
quicker one, fired in on leg stump, Smith gets back and flicks for one
changed of pace, tossed up gently on middle and off, Kemp plods it back
tossed up on middle and off, Kemp defends and the ball dribbles to square leg
fuller, middle and leg, Kemp sweeps hard out to deep backward square leg
tossed up outside off, Kemp drives it to mid-off
tossed up on off stump, Smith likes the line and sweeps through the gap at midwicket and with no fielder there he gets four
tossed up wide, Smith gets back but mistimes the cut to point
tossed up full on middle and off, Smith defends coming forward
a fraction too short and Smith chops into the covers for one
quicker delivery on middle and leg, Kemp gets a good stride in and defends
dropped,though it was tough. Tossed up wide, Smith gets across off and plays at it, getting a thick edge which Akmal doesnt read, and the ball clips his pad to run fine

crucial moment! Kemp gets a big stride in, pushing the ball into the covers, Smith calls for the run but realizes he's struggling, then dives full stretch but he cant beat a fine effort from Malik, collecting and firing in a good throw to Akmal, mid-air, to get Smith way short of his crease ... you have to say that run wasnt really on
tossed up on middle and leg, turned to midwicket for one
nice loop and drift, tossed up on middle and off, Kemp prods forward into the covers and smartly resists the single this time
tossed up again, he gets forward and defends
full and outside off stump, driven across to long-on
flat, spinning in from outside off,  gets a bit of bat and pad as he pushes forward in defense
comes down the track but Malik drags back the length and he pushes it out to the on side
quickish turn from outside off, sharp turn too and Kemp is struck on the pad, outside off, as he tries to chop it away to the off side
fuller, outside off and Kemp fails to connect with his sweep shot
slower, on the off stump line, defended on the front foot
tossed-up, outside off and Boucher stretches across to defend
on the off and middle, a tad short in length, worked to right of midwicket for a single
Tossed-up, outside off stump and Kemp goes down on his knee to slog sweep it high over deep midwicket
Arm-ball on the off stump line, chopped away to the off side
Leans forward to drive to long on
Turns in from outside off, Boucher goes back to work it to wide midwicket
Turns in from outside off, Boucher goes back to work it to wide midwicket
On the middle and leg, quick and flat, Kemp inside-edges a swing across the line
Fuller, on the off and middle, driven to long-on for a single
Shuffles across and tries to swing across the line and again gets a inside edge to short fine leg region
Spinning down the leg side, tries to flick it away and it brushes the pad enrouter to Akmal
Comes down the track and heaves a flighted delivery to wide midwicket. Very good fielding there by Misbah
Spinning down the leg side, he tries to sweep but can't connect
And again. This time he tries to help it to the leg side..
Fuller, outside off, turned past square leg
Beaten.  Lands full in length , on the off and middle and spins viciously past the outside ege
Beaten. Slightly short in length, boucher is beaten on the cut
short again, cut to deep point
short in length again, turning away, cut to Gul at short third man region for a quick single
arm-ball outside off stump, beaten on the cut shot
starts off with a yorker on the middle and off stumps line, punched down to mid-on and they scamper through for a single. Bad piece of fielding there
fuller length delivery outside the off stump, driven down to long-off for a single, this one came much easier
fraction short and Kemp cuts it behind point for an easy single
forced away off the back-foot through cover point, yet another easy single added to the total
again driven down the ground, easy single
full and drifting in, Boucher gets behind the line and punches it back to the bowler
there he goes! tossed up outside the off stump, Kemp dances down the track, Good clean hit
quicker delivery, punched away towards cover
another tight delivery, forced away towards cover, again no single
tossed up and close to the off stump line, Kemp goes down on on knee and sweeps it down to fine leg for a brace. Excellent piece of fielding in the deep says two runs
quicker delivery, defended
again swept away, just a single on this occasion
short in length, spinning away and Kemp goes on the back foot to punch it to right of long-off where Yaseer moves smartly to swoop on the ball quickly and restricts it to just a single.
short in length, spinning away from Boucher who plays a late cut and Sohail Tanveer makes a good stop at short third man region
stands tall to punch it to long on for a single
on the off stump line, cut to point
picks up a single with a drive to long on
slider does the trick. Kemp charged out to a length delivery on the middle stump, aiming to swing over long--on but the ball slid in, through the bat and pad gap and crashed into the furniture.
short in length ,cut past point for a single
short again, Albie stays back to punch it to long-on
fuller, slower, sliding down leg side and Boucher is struck on the pad in front of middle and leg line
quicker, fullish, outside off stump, Boucher is beaten on the cut- not the length for it
slower now, short in length though and that allows Boucher to swat it towards long-on
defended on the front foot
full and outside off, it was the googly and Boucher goes for a slog sweep but misses it completely
legbreak on the middle stump line, Boucher gets a leading edge to the off side as he tries to play across the line
here comes the slider and it cramps up Boucher before striking him on the pad, going down leg side though
big leg spin. It drifted in, landed on the middle and leg before turning right across a squared-up Boucher and he got a leading edge to the off side
tossed up on the off stump line, slog swept away for a single
short in length, lands outside off stump and spins away, cut to right of sweeper cover
short again, and outside off stump, cut powerfully but Pakistan are fielding like champions today. Malik throws himself to his right at cover to make a fine stop
slows up the pace, flighted delivery just outside off, slog swept to deep midwicket
he has been guilty of bowling short and this one sits up outside leg stump and Albie pulls it to long leg boundary
short in length, turning in towards middle stump, Albie stays on the back foot and punches it to long-on

flighted delivery, on the middle stump line, Boucher cleared the front foot and tried to swing it across the line, against the turn and it swirled towards mid-off region where Malik gets across to take a tumbling catch.
comes in quick with the arm, chopped away to the off side
legbreak on the leg and middle line, turned to right of midwicket for a single
delivered from the front of the hand, full and on the middle stump line, steered to cover point for a single
faster one and it slips down the leg side and Akmal can't get across in time
Caught and bowled. Tame dismissal. It was a loopy flighted delivery, full and on the middle stump line, Pollock pushed at it, couldn't keep it down and it went straight to Afridi.
well outside off stump and cut to deep point. That's the end of a rather fine spell from Afridi. He varied his pace and turn cleverly.
fullish, yorker length, worked to midwicket for a single
off cutter, just outside off stump, not all that short but Albie stays back to square cut it past backward point.
full toss, well outside off stump, Albie reaches for it, makes contact with the bottom-half of the bat and it rolls to point
full and outside off, drilled to long-on
full and swinging in, full toss, turned to deep midwicket

Albie, the bighitter, is gone. slow off cutter, around 124 kmph, full and on the middle stump line, Albie went for a lofted shot down the ground but the off cutter meant the ball spun a bit and the ball went towards long-off. Its safely pouched just before the ropes.
yorker outside off stump, guided to point
short in length, on the off and middle, steered to cover point
full and outside off stump, shaping away and Botha is beaten, going for a big off drive
yorker outside off stump, Botha tries to chop it to third man but misses
another yorker, on the middle and off stump line, stabbed away to cover point
on a length, just outside off stump, jabbed on to the pad
inswinging yorker, on the off stump line, jabbed to backward point
length delivery this time, outside off and driven uppishly to left of long-off where Younis Khan runs across to make a diving stop
fullish, on the middle and leg, turned past square leg
slower one, Botha skips down the track and has a heave across the line and was beaten by the change of the pace. The ball went just over the middle stump
yorker, on the middle stump line, stabbed away towards mid-on for a single
done in by the slower one. Delivered like a off break, it landed just outside off, on a length and broke in to evade the swing across the line
yorker ends up as a low full toss, driven to long-on
cleans him up with a nip-backer. It landed on a length, around the off stump and shaped in. Ntini went for a slog across the line, missed and the middle stump was pegged back.

inn2.comm: right on target: The pollock line and the length. Just outside off and on a good length, left alone. Pakistan's troubles have been at the top
relatively quicker and it cuts in off a length to strike him on the pad, but it was going down leg side
on a length, just outside off stump, defended on the front foot
In the zone outside off stump and he lets that one fly past him to Boucher
on a length again - metronomic as ever, coming in a touch, on the middle and leg, jabbed away to the on side
that's a good delivery. A legcutter, on the off and middle and Yasir is squared-up as he pushes forward and gets a thickish outside edge to third man
on a length, just outside off stump, Yasir goes back and across to punch it to mid-off
slips way down the leg side as he tries to bring the back in and Boucher dives full stretch to his left to make the stop
fuller, straighter and it comes in from just outside off, Yasir lunges at it, his left leg across and he has to try getting his bat around it, fails and is hit on the thigh pad
again he lunges across, pushes at it and gets a inside-edge to the pad. He is getting that front leg too much across. It could be risky
and again. Its a nip-backer and it cuts in, Yasir tries to stop his front foot movement, get his bat in line but is beaten for the pace and the ball crashes into the thigh pad
full and outside off stump this time, left alone
fuller but drifting towards the pad and flicked past square leg
huge roar goes up Afridi gets ready to face the first ball. Its a length delivery, holding its line on the off stump and Afridi steers to point
on a length, on the middle and leg, turned past square leg
length delivery, lands on the middle and off, moves in, worked to midwicket
on a length, on the middle and leg, turned around the corner, straight to Ntini short fine leg

There he goes. Over long-on in style. It was a length delivery, just outside off stump, coming in a touch, Afridi leaned forward to punch it on the up and up she soared over long-on boundary. Stunning hit.
crashed through the off side. Another length delivery, outside off and Afridi forces it on the up through cover
from wide of the crease, lands on a length, just outside off stump and again Yasir's left leg is plonked right across, again he has to try play around it and is struck on the pad
just outside off, off a length, holding its line, guided to third man.

dropped by Kallis at first and the only slip. It was a length delivery that held its line outside off stump and Afridi hopped back and was troubled by the straightening. He pushed at it and got a edge to Kallis who clangs it. A absolute sitter, a dolly and he has put it down.
again that left leg is pushed across and he is struck on the thigh pad. He is in trouble here. Footwork is messed up.
outside the off stump, a length delivery and Yasir gets into a tangle with his foot movement and stabs at it and is beaten
gets behind the line of this one - a length delivery just outside off, coming in - and pushes it to cover
lands on the good length area, just outside off stump and holds its line, Afridi pushes it to the off side.
just over the off stump. It landed on a length, on the off stump and came back in, Afridi tried to swing across the line, a short-arm jab and misses it completely. He is pretty angry with himself
length delivery zipping past the off stump and he shoulders arms
on a length, around the off stump, Yasir stays back to punch it to the off side
off cutter, coming in from just outside off stump and Yasir is again into a tangle with that left foot movement and is struck on the thigh pad.
whack. Fullish, outside the off stump and Afridi went through with the line and sliced it over cover.
corrects his length, on a good length this time, on the middle and leg, Afridi tries to turn it to on side, misses and it runs off the pad
lands short of length, climbs up as it comes in and defended to the on side
full in length, outside off stump, comes in a touch and Yasir gets a edge to the pad as he pushes forward and across to defend
short in length, on the off and middle, coming in and Yasir gets going with a short-arm pull to long leg
fuller, on a length, outside off stump and stays there, left alone
outside off stump, on a length, steered to backward point
drifting towards pads and Afridi helps it along to the long leg boundary. The fine leg was in the circle.
Afridi goes downtown. A flat six over long-on. It landed on a length, on the off and middle, came in a touch and Afridi just knifed through the line. Imperious strike.
A slower one and Afridi gets a inside edge past the leg stump. It landed outside off stump, came in and Afridi lunged at it. Lemon cut.
fuller, on the middle and leg, Afridi whips it to midwicket. He is on 32 from just 17 balls. The crowd roar in approval. They want more.

They won't as Smith takes a very good catch at mid-off. It was another slower one, just outside off stump and Afridi drilled it uppishly to the right of mid-off where Smith lunged to his right to take a very sharp catch. That was travelling at some speed and he did well to cup his palms around it.
lands on a length, outside off stump, comes in a touch and is left alone
fuller and Yasir is almost trapped in front. Again that lunge across, the left leg gets too far and he falls over a touch but is struck just outside off stump
again struck on the pad, just outside off stump. Another lunge across the line and the bat fails to come around the front pad. He is living rather dangerously
from wide of the crease, full in length, just outside off stump, defended on the front foot
slips down the leg side and Boucher makes a fine diving stop
on the off stump line, punched to left of point. Good diving stop there
lands on a length, outside off and comes in, Younis leans forward and steers to point
shorter in length and that allows Younis to punch through cover point for couple of runs
fuller, on the off and midde line, Younis shuffles across and works it to short midwicket
flies past the gully fielder. A legcutter, well outside off stump and Younis went searching, bat away from the body and he pushed it to right of a diving Kallis
off cutter, slower in pace, just outside off stump and punched to mid-on
hits the deck, short of length, on the middle stump and Yasir, again falling over a touch, manages to turn it to short midwicket
shuffles across, gets in line of a full pitched delivery on the off stump and drives hard but straight to mid-off
slipping down leg side, Younis tries his best to swing it away but no wood on leather
on a length, around the middle stump line, turned to the on side
creamed through cover. Full and well outside off stump and Yasir leans across to drill it through cover.
closer to the off stump and driven to mid-off
homing in on the off stump, pushed to the on side
fuller, on the off and middle, flicked across the line to left of square leg where Botha fumbles
on a length, just outside off stump, pushed to cover.
slower, off cutter, full and on the off stump, defended on the front foot to the on side
on the middle and leg and Yasir whips it through midwicket.
outside off stump this time and Yasir plays it quietly into the cover region
on the off stump line, coming in a touch and Yasir works it to right of square leg. There was a chance of single there but misunderstanding between the two denies Yasir a single
he will get it this time, another wristy stroke past square leg and will retain strike
full in length, on the middle stump line, Yasir stretches across and flicks across the line to square leg.
on the off and middle, full in length, punched to mid-on. Pak need 142 to win
fuller, on the middle and off, coming in and Yasir whips it across the line past square leg.
And he is caught at cover point. Full and outside off stump, Yasir reaches out for it and ends up slicing it in the air to left of Kallis who takes a tumbling catch. The openers are back in the hutch
on the off stump line, Yousuf eases it to backward point
length delivery that bounces a bit, outside off, Yousuf pushes at it, bat away from the body and gets a inside edge and the ball bounces over the stumps. Hmm...
on the middle and leg, full in length, turned to long leg
around the off stump line, defended to cover with the full face of the bat
on the middle, drifting towards middle and leg, Yousuf wrists it away to deep backward square leg. Nice use of the wrists.
on the pads, tickled to Ntini at short fine leg
outside off stump, off a length and Yousuf punches it through backward point to wide third man region for a single.
slower one, delivered like a off break, full and just outside off stump, eased to mid-on
full and outside off stump, left alone
on a length, outside off stump, punched to Gibbs at cover
sliding down the leg side, helped along to Pollock at fine leg
on the off stump line, pushed to Gibbs at cover
fuller, just outside off stump, mistimes a drive to mid-on
on a length, just outside off stump, Younis gets forward, opens the bat-face and steers it to point.
beaten Full in length, just outside off stump and holding its line, Yousuf has a tentative poke at it
full in length, on the middle, pushed down the track
fullpitched outside off stump and Yousuf goes down on his knee to drive pleasingly to cover
leans forward to dead bat a length delivery to the off side. Pak need 135 at 3.8 runs per over
fuller, just short of the blockhole, jabbed away to point
slower, homing in on the off stump, Yousuf stays back to turn it to point
a tad short in length and bit of width outside off and Younis whiplashes it through backward point. Cracking stroke.

just outside off stump, pushed close towards backward point and sets for a nonexistent run. Yousuf is not interested in suicide and sends him back. Younis gets back to his crease in a hurry and puts up his hand to apologize
slower one on the off and middle, defended to the on side
fullish, on the middle stump line, flicked to short midwicket
shorter, just outside off stump, coming in and Younis runs it down to third man
short one this time, well over the batsman's head

that's a smart catch from Botha. on the pads and Younis filcks to short midwicket, Botha is prowling there, dives to his right and pulls off a good two-handed take. That gives South Africa a big boost, Younis is gone immediately after drinks and there's an opening here. Not a great ball from Morkel but it produces a wicket
full and just outside off, pushed forward
full again, pushed forward, straight to mid-on
yorker this time, angling into the legs and forces Malik to dig it out, well bowled that time.
full and on off, driven to cover, that's a fine wicket maiden from Morkel
slower one from Langeveldt, loops in almost, Yousuf decides to pat it to the off side, the line has been straight from South Africa
135.3 kph this time, driven down the ground to mid-on
short of a length, Langeveldt mixing it up well here, Yousuf defends watchfully
another slower one, just 117kph, no two deliveries are identical (no twins), Yousuf pats back again
tucked to the off side, good passage of play for South Africa
from wide of the crease, on the pads, turned away for a leg bye, tight over
patted back down the ground, good long stride from Malik
slightly slower, tucked to the on side
short and ducked under it
full and outside off stump, defended to cover
A slow off cutter, homing in on the off stump, pushed to the off sider.
just outside off, off a length, tapped to third man region
short and outside off stump, steered to third man for a single
fuller, straighter, on the off and middle, driven to mid-on
just outside off, fullish and Yousuf glides forward to guide it to third man

almost run out. short in length, on the middle and leg, turned to right of midwicket where Smith swooped on the ball and had a shy at the striker's end. Not too far from the stumps and Yousuf was short of the crease
short of length, just outside off, steered to third man
closer to the off stump, on a length, late cut to third man
on the middle and leg, turned past square leg for a single
fullish, on the middle and leg, whipped to long leg and Ntini gets across to make the stop
full and on the off and middle, eased to the off side.
outside off and Yousuf moves towards the line and dabs it to third man region for yet another single.
closer to the off stump, Malik shuffles across and nudges it to the off side
on the off stump line, coming in, short in length and that allows Malik to stand tall and whip it across, past square leg for a single
spins in from outside off stump, Malik goes back to push it to the on side.
fuller and Malik leans forward to drive with the turn to long-on
tosses it well outside off stump and Yousuf stretches forward to push it to cover
again lands well outside off, on a length and turns in, Yousuf is struck on the pad as he tries to work it with the turn
And again.

deja-vu at Faisalabad. Botha, after bowling the first two deliveries on the stumps, has shifted to landing it outside the off stump. There is turn on offer here and he doesn't want to start it from the stumps.
lands on a length, outside off stump and Malik chops it to third man for a single
fuller, outside off stump and driven to sweeper cover for a single. Pak need 114 at 4.1 runs per over.
another dab to third man. Malik has been doing that consistently.
on the middle and Yousuf, being a wristy batsman, turns it past square leg
fuller, on the yorker length, just outside off stump and Malik jabs it away
fullish, outside off stump and square driven to sweeper cover
leans forward and drives with the turn and Botha dives to his right to make a stop
Malik breaks free with a lofted shot over long-on. He waltzes down the track, reached the pitch and swung it over the ropes
picks up a single with a drive through the on side
full and outside off, turning in and Yousuf stretches across, waits for the turn and turns it behind square leg for a single
It's Malik's turn to pick a single behind square leg
leans forward to a delivery pitched further outside off stump and drives to sweeper cover. The two are playing pretty calmly out there. South Africa need a breakthrough.
full pitched outside off stump and Yousuf drives to deep cover for a single
full again, on the off stump, driven to mid-off
beaten Trying to dab another one to third man. It was close to the off stump and he was cramped up
full in length, on the off stump, driven to cover.
full again, on the off stump, pushed to mid-off
full pitched, on the off stump again, pushed to cover
on the middle stump line, turned to the on side
on the off stump, turning in, leans forward to work it to square leg
almost run out. On the middle, turned to right of de Villiers at midwicket and he was not able to get a direct hit in. By the time Boucher collected and broke the stumps, Yousuf was in
no ball. free hit coming up next. turned to square leg. This should be interesting
doesn't make use of it as he comes down the track and heaves to long-on
from round the stumps, full and outside off, steered to backward point
length delivery outside off stump, punched to backward point
on a length, on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket
slower, off break action, full and outside off stump, guided to backward point
homing in on the off stump, Yousuf leans forward to defend. Kallis is keeping it tight. On and around the off stump.
on the off and middle, worked to Gibbs at midwicket
short in length, off cutter, on the off and middle, pushed to cover
tossed outside off stump, doosra, defended on the front foot
quicker, on the off and middle, Malik goes back quickly to jab it to square leg
from round the stumps to Yousuf. Full and outside off stump, turning in to clip the bat and pad
slightly short in length, Yousuf goes back and turns it to backward square leg
flighted, fuller, just outside off, driven back to Botha
again full and just outside off, dabbed to the on side
slightly short in length, just outside off stump, Malik opens the bat-face and taps it to left of third man
closer to the off stump and Yousuf plays it to point.
Yousuf's first boundary of the innings. He walked out and hit a length delivery on the up past Kallis.
And he picks up a single. Tip and run. On the off and middle, he drops it close on the off side and rushes across for a single
shuffles across towards off stumps and flicks a delivery on middle and off to long leg

short in length, outside off stump, tries to dab it to third man - he has doing that the whole day really - but misses it this time and is beaten. Kallis appeals as an afterthought while Boucher doesn't bother to clear his throat
goes back to work a ball on the middle through midwicket
fuller, outside off and turned with the turn to backward square leg
on the off stump line, nudged to the on side and Boucher runs to pick the ball
on the middle and off, turning in, turned to deep midwicket
floated full in length, on the middle, driven to right of long -on
slow loopy full toss outside off stump and Yousuf stretches across to square drive it to left of sweeper cover
on a length, coming in towards off stump, punched to the bowler
slower one, on the off stump line, driven to the on side
off cutter, on the middle and off, turned to midwicket. 80 to win at 4.1 runs per over
shorter in length, just outside off stump, pushed to backward point. Malik wants a single but is sent back by Yousuf
slower, fuller, outside off, square driven to de Villiers at backward point
on the off and middle, pushed, along the ground,  past a lunging Kallis for a single
off cutter, outside off stump and Yousuf stays back to tap it to third man
length delivery on the off stump, punched to mid-off. btw.. Boucher is standing up to the stumps
fuller, straighter, on the middle, pushed towards midwicket. He didn't get forward, just stood there and worked it to the on side
lands on a length, just outside off, shapes in and Malik pushes it quietly to the off side.
off cutter, slightly short in length and Malik stands up tall to punch it past the diving midwicket fielder for a single
on the off stump line, off a length and nudged dabbed steered guided and what not to backward point
shuffles across to the off stump and clips a ball on the middle and off to backward square leg. He has done it at least twice to Kallis, shuffling right across the sticks.
no shuffling this time, just leans forward to push a length delivery to cover
And here comes the dab to third man. Just outside off stump, Malik waits on the ball before chopping it late
fuller, outside off stump, slashed away to third man for a single.
on the off and middle, coming in, Malik goes back to nurdle it to the on side
off cutter ,on the off and middle, punched to long-on for a single. Drinks on the field
on the middle and leg, worked to midwicket
short in length, holding its line outside off stump and Malik plays his favourite dab to third man
on the middle and leg and Yousuf tries to glance it but is struck on the pad
comes in after landing on a length, just outside off stmp and Yousuf waits for the ball to break in before steering it to left of backward point
on the middle and off line, Malik turns it to midwicket
fuller, outside off stump, Malik is late to pick up the length and lunges at the last minute as he tries to drive through the off side and gets a inside edge to the on
on a length, on the off and middle, pushed to the off side
harder ball and it bounces a touch, on the off stump line, steered to backward point
off cutter, outside off stump, driven to cover
strays on to the middle and leg and Yousuf flicks it away for a single
on the middle and off, off a length, defended down the track
short in length, on the hips, clipped uppishly past square leg for a single
off cutter, on the off and middle line, Malik leans forward to pick up a single with a drive to long-on. The game is meandering at a leisurely pace
shout for lbw as Pollock gets one to spin in like a off break, full and on the middle and Yousuf is struck on the pad, trying to work it across the line. It would have probably turned down leg.
another off break, full and on the middle and off line, flicked past square leg
on the middle and off stump line, turned to midwicket
full and outside off stump, holds its line and Malik is beaten as he pushes inside the line, thinking the ball would cut in
off cutter, on the off and middle, punched down the track
on the middle and leg, going down leg and Yousuf tries to pull it away and it runs off the pad to left of Boucher
full and slipping down leg side, flicked away and Pak need 63 runs now.
Ah! the late cut. On a length, outside off stump and Malik pings the third man region
full and outside off stump, Yousuf slashes it to wide third man and by the time Kemp gets across they pick up two runs
short in length, on the off and middle, whipped past square leg
fullish, outside off stump, square driven to sweeper cover for a single
short in length, outside off stump, cut away to third man.
fullish and Malik drives powerfully and it crashes into the Langeveld't right boot
Malik doesn't want you to read it and brings some excitement by crashing a full-pitched delivery over extra cover
on the hips, clipped past square leg
That break is followed up with a wicket. Short in length, outside off, holding its line a touch and Malik goes for a square cut but ends up nicking it behind

dropped by de Villiers at point. Short in length again, outside off stump, cut uppishly and it was dipping in front of de Villiers who swooped quickly but couldn't get his palms around it. The ball was dipping rapidly
full in length, on the stumps, driven to the off side
banged in short and pulled away to fine leg where Langeveldt rushes across to make a fine diving stop
fuller, on the middle and leg, Misbah is struck on the pad as he fails to connect with his flick
lands outside off stump, turns in, cut to deep point
turning in from outside off stump, pushed for a single
full and outside off stump, turning in slightly and Misbah is struck on the front pad, outside the off stump. Boucher and Botha appeal but nope.. that can't be given
another shout for lbw. Much better shout this time. It landed on the off stump and struck Yousuf in front of middle. It was turning, the umpire must have thought it would have turned down leg. Close.
doosra and it spins past the forward prod offered by YOusuf
leans forward to place a full length delivery to cover point
short in length, on the off stump line, defended to the backward point region
full in length, on the off and middle, driven to Pollock at long-on
on the off stump line, slower in pace, steered to third man
fullish, on the middle stump line, yorker length, driven straight dwon the ground and Albie dives to make a stop and quickly has a shy at the striker's end
tossed up full on middle and leg, turned around the corner into the gap, good throw comes in from Smith at short fine leg but Yousuf is safe
on the middle and leg, turned to square leg for a single
leans forward to defend
sharp turn and Yousuf is cut into half. It landed on the off stump and spun sharply and went between the bat and pad and over the stumps
leans forward to drive it back to the bowler
full and outside off, square driven
lands on a length, outside off stump, comes in and Misbah chops it on to his pad.
on the off stump line, punched to midwicket. 37 to win from 45 balls.
just outside off stump and Misbah punches it to Pollock at long-on
slightly short in length, outside off stump, Yousuf cuts but de Villiers dives to his left to make the stop
on the off stump, off a length, Yousuf stands up tall to punch it to sweeper cover
floated outside off and Yousuf picks up a single with a drive to long-off
low full toss and Misbah drives to long-on for yet another single. 33 to win from 40 balls
full and on a driveable length, outside off stump, square driven to sweeper cover
from wide round the stumps, full and on the middle, jabbed back to the bowler
on the middle stump line, whipped past square leg and they run hard to come back for the second run
fullish, on the middle and leg, again whipped past square leg, Misbah wants two but Yousuf sends him back as the long leg fielder swoops in on the ball
on a length, coming in towards off and middle, pushed close on the off side and Yousuf calls Misbah for a quick single. Good running between the wickets. Yousuf is on 49
short in length, cut to point
slower, fuller, outside off stump, Yousuf goes for a off drive but gets a inside edge to midwicket
56th ODI fifty up. Full and outside off stump, Yousuf leans forward to guide it through the vacant slip region. 51 from 104 balls with one four.
short in length, on the middle stump line and Yousuf pulls it to deep square leg region
off cutter, fullish, on the off stump line, driven to long-on
flighted delivery outside off stump, steered to cover point for a single
lands outside off stump, and Misbah is struck on the pad in front of off and middle Misbah was stretching well forward.
lands on a length, on the middle, turns in, goes back to punch it to right of Botha who makes a diving stop
lands just outside leg stump and Yousuf is struck on the pad as he fails to connect with his sweep. Botha appeals but that can't be given
retains the strike with a drive to long-on
on the off stump line, off a length, pushed to point.
on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket
Albie is keeping it tight. Full in length, on the off and middle, wicket to wicket bowling and Misbah punches it back at him
commentator's curse strikes. This one is a full toss, on the middle stump and Misbah drills it straight down the ground
shorter and pulled away for a single
on a length, coming in towards off stump, Yousuf steers it to backward point region. The ball struck the pad first and Albie goes up in appeal but the point of impact was outside off stump.
leans forward to work a flighted delivery past square leg for a single
Floated outside off stump, full in length and Misbah went down on his knee to carve it high to wide long-on region
driven to cover
on the middle and leg, wristed past square leg for a single
flighted delivery - he is still operatingd from round the stumps, Yousuf inside-edges a drive and it runs to square leg
slips down the leg side and that beats the batsman and the 'keeper
And Yousuf teases the crowd with a perfect forward defensive stroke!

There comes the winning hit. Thunderous six over long-on. Full in length, on the off and middle and Misbah, who sparkled in the Twenty20 cup with some big hitting, swung it over the ropes. Pakistan lead the five-match series 2-1
